    <div class="content">
        <h1>Sustainable Fishing</h1>

        <h2>The Importance of Sustainable Fishing</h2>
        <p>The viability of fish populations and the condition of our seas depend on sustainable fishing methods. Fish populations are quickly declining due to overfishing and irresponsible fishing methods, making the future of global fisheries questionable. Sustainable fishing practices are crucial for the health of our oceans and marine life.</p>
        <div class="image-placeholder">Image: Sustainable fishing practices</div>

        <h2>The Need for Sustainable Fishing</h2>
        <p>As the demand for seafood rises, the world is becoming increasingly concerned about overfishing. Fish populations are declining as a result of unsustainable fishing methods, endangering the wellbeing of our seas and the livelihoods of those who depend on them. More than ever, the need for sustainable fishing methods exists, and achieving them will involve cooperation from the public sector, private sector, and end users.</p>
        <div class="image-placeholder">Image: Effects of overfishing</div>

        <h2>Evolution of Fishing Practices</h2>
        <p>After World War II, the marine fishery sector evolved into a commercial industrial fishery, using larger fishing gear and vessels in an effort to bolster economies. This led to an increase in marine harvest worldwide, but many fisheries collapsed due to overexploitation. Industrial fishing gear, such as purse seines and bottom trawls, significantly damaged marine habitats and produced bycatch.</p>
        <div class="image-placeholder">Image: Industrial fishing vessels</div>

        <h2>Current Efforts and Future Direction</h2>
        <p>Stricter laws and fewer industrial fleets have contributed to a decrease in bycatch, although these measures are still unsustainable. Pole and line fishing is being promoted as a sustainable practice due to increased customer interest in responsibly caught seafood. Future fisheries management ought to emphasize small-scale, regional, ecosystem-based strategies that make use of local expertise and involvement.</p>
        <div class="image-placeholder">Image: Sustainable fishing methods</div>
